headline.main: Ukraine Takes Russia to UN Court Over Rebel Funding, Crimea
headline.print_headline: Ukraine Takes Russia to UN Court Over Rebel Funding, Crimea

lead_paragraph: Ukraine's deputy foreign minister on Monday accused Russia of financing terrorism by shipping arms, ammunition and funds to separatist rebels in eastern Ukraine and of discriminating against non-Russians in the annexed Crimean Peninsula.
